                    "name": "Graph-RAG",
                    "mode": "graph",
                    "response": "# The Birth of Wukong (The Monkey King)\n\nThe birth of Sun Wukong, also known as the Monkey King, is a fascinating episode rooted deeply in Chinese mythology and the tale of *Journey to the West*. According to the details provided, his origin is miraculous and highly symbolic, intertwined with the natural and cosmic order.\n\n## Origin from the Immortal Stone\n\nWukong’s birth is described as emerging from a supernatural source: the Immortal Stone (仙石) that resides atop the Flower-Fruit Mountain (花果山). This stone itself is a divine entity, charged with cosmic energy directly linked to the mythical geography of the Eastern Victory Divine Continent (东胜神洲). It is said that an egg from this stone was produced under mysterious circumstances, from which the Stone Monkey (石猴), the future Great Monkey King, hatched. This origin aligns Wukong with the primal forces of nature and the cosmos, symbolizing purity and a connection to the spiritual world beyond mere mortals.\n\nThe scene where the Stone Monkey discovers the Water Curtain Cave (水帘洞洞天) as his kingdom further signifies his sovereignty and unique status among the other monkeys. This cave under a waterfall becomes his home and a sacred locale in the myth.\n\n## Divine and Cosmic Recognition\n\nWukong’s birth and awakening are so extraordinary that they attract the attention of the highest celestial authority, the Jade Emperor (玉皇大天尊玄穹高上帝). The Jade Emperor commands his divine attendants, Thousand-Mile Eye (千里眼) and Wind-Following Ear (顺风耳), to observe the golden light emitted by the Stone Monkey. This light symbolizes the vitality and divine essence of Wukong, confirming his unique origin and heralding his future significance.\n\nThe description states that the Stone Monkey was born of the essence of Heaven and Earth (天地精华), reinforcing his nature as a being intimately connected to the cosmic forces. He is a miraculous life form that embodies both natural and supernatural qualities.\n\n## Transformation into the Monkey King\n\nAfter his birth, the Stone Monkey does not remain passive. He quickly learns to walk, jump, and explore, showcasing both intelligence and vitality. His leadership among the monkeys grows as he leads them to settle in the Water Curtain Cave, where they express joy and allegiance to him as their king.\n\nThe Stone Monkey later adopts the grand title \"Great Sage Equal to Heaven\" (齐天大圣), reflecting his aspiration to transcend mortal limits, pursue immortality, and challenge the order of heaven.\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Birthplace:** Flower-Fruit Mountain (花果山), specifically from an Immortal Stone egg.\n- **Nature:** Supernaturally born from cosmic essence, bridging heaven and earth.\n- **Recognition:** Observed and acknowledged by the Jade Emperor and his divine envoys.\n- **Development:** Quickly learns and leads a tribe of monkeys, establishing his rule.\n- **Significance:** Symbolizes a natural and mystical origin, setting the stage for his later quest for immortality and enlightenment.\n\nThis rich and symbolic narrative establishes Wukong as a unique figure born of cosmic forces, destined for greatness and spiritual transformation. His birth story is a cornerstone of his legend in *Journey to the West* and Chinese mythology at large.",
